Peter Jennings, the iconic ABC News anchor, has been diagnosed with lung cancer and will undergo chemotherapy.
Despite his illness, he plans to continue anchoring "World News Tonight" when possible.
Jennings, along with Dan Rather and Tom Brokaw, represented a bygone era of network news dominance.
The departure of these anchors marks a shift in television journalism.
While Jennings battles cancer, ABC News faces the challenge of maintaining viewer loyalty amidst a changing media landscape.
His personal battle with the disease has touched many, showcasing his resilience and dedication to his craft.
